# PHL Development Rules

All AI agents working on any PHL project must read and follow:

**📋 [docs/doc_architecture.md](../../docs/doc_architecture.md)** — Canonical ecosystem architecture, project layout, API contracts, deployment model.

**📋 [docs/doc_ai_planning_mode.md](../../docs/doc_ai_planning_mode.md)** — Planning workflow: always produce a High-Level Technical Contract and wait for approval before implementing.

**📋 [docs/doc_verification_guide.md](../../docs/doc_verification_guide.md)** — Verification paths for every change type.

## Key Directives

- **Never implement without a plan.** Use `doc_ai_planning_mode.md` as the workflow.
- **Never change an API endpoint without updating `phlara/apis`.** That repo is the source of truth for dashboard consumers.
- **Never commit `.env` or secrets.** Keys live on the VPS only.
- **Never force-push to `main`.** It deploys to production immediately.
- **Single source of truth for agents/skills:** `ai-specs/` — symlinked to `.claude/`, `.cursor/`, `.codex/`.